rComments: MATH 285 was the first mathematica course and the last MATH course i had to take for engineering.  I was afraid on the first day of class, but Denka really helped me overcome my fears, and enjoy the class a lot.  Denka is very intelligent and passionate; she had 3 office hours per week and was really helpful in relating math to the real world.

Take a look at available Calc 3 professors and choose someone other than her. I can't stand this university hiring people who can't speak English. It shouldn't come down to you teaching yourself math, then what are we paying for? Diversity may be a good thing, but only if they speak English.

Really not as bad a professor as most think. I did end up having to teach myself Calc III, but it wasn't much more than a couple hours each week before a quiz and then a cram session before an exam. The curves are pretty nice and shouldn't be too hard to get at least a B.

Oh...what to say about Denka... First and foremost, she talks to the board. Also, the first exam she gave my class had a lot of WTF action going on, because she made it RIDICULOUSLY hard. I'd seen the same exam she gave the previous semester, and they weren't even remotely similar. Sweet lady, but hard to understand. Get someone else if you can.
I like her but her class is really hard. I failed most of her exams. But she gives a great curve, so I still did well over all!

she sucked, i couldnt understand her at all and all she did was proofs, she hardly ever did any examples in lecture. I went to lecture even tho i was clueless as to what was going on. the only reason i got a B+ is because my TA was amazing...he actually spoke english

By far, the worst teacher I have ever had. In class, all she does is prove the theorems in he book. I learned absolutely nothing. There were on average 20 kids in the class per day. No one liked her. I actually taught myself Calc 3 by reading the book. She was completely useless.

She is a very nice lady, but it is very hard to understand her sometimes. Her lectures are all over the place. Luckily my TA was pretty good. I kinda had to teach myself the material from the textbook. The tests were ok, the final was hard, but there is a curve.
Difficult to understand at times. I realized too late in the semester that it's better to just skip lecture and have the t.a. explain it all during discussion...
Do yourself a favor and get the other professor...trust me!
I had her in a big lecture before and I didnt find all lectures too clear. However in a small class setting this lady was awesome. She was EXTREMELY helpful. Go to office hours :)
Not easy to follow in class. Luckily I had a good TA. But the material was easy enough to learn from the book.

she seems like a nice lady, but doesn't make any sense. it's like she's copying theorms from the book and you don't really understand how to do book problems. you have to read the chapters and figure out what's going on yourself- which is not fun.

Denka...She's a funny lady, but I could never follow her work. Luckily, I had taken Calc in high school. Most of the stuff she lectured about had to be re-taught by the T.A. I guess her class wasn't too bad. The weekly quizzes and the 4 exams were pretty straight-forward.
She is very funny if you listen carefully.  I enjoyed her rambling.  Made the class more interesting.  I would take another class with her.

She did ramble on about some things, overall her class wasn't too difficult if you kept up. We had weekly quizes trhat were pretty easy. Her lectures did tend to get a little boring, but overall I liked her and owuld take another class with her at the professor.

Rather easy professor, exams never had anything extremely difficult. Not a good lecturer though, rambles on about things that are unimportant, and says “you will learn more about this in (insert class)” too often.  Accent isn’t too bad.
Rambles

I took this course Mathematica. Denka didn't know how to use the software. So she opted to lecture once a week. I learned better when she did opposed to on the computer. She's funny and tests were super easy.
